item.itunes:summary:
On this episode me and Tony talk with the Cool Kids. They're from the Chi and were a seminal part of the new wave of Chicago hip hop. They set a blueprint for how to build a fanbase on the internet. They split a few years back and recently reunited. We actually recorded this one a few months ago and I had to listen for some edits and it was really fun. We talked about their rise and obstacles and also the conversation somehow veered to sex robot philosophy. We freestyled and made some goofy songs. It's a fun ep.
@thecoolxkids @chuckisdope @sirmichaelrocks
